## For later
- Add option for allowing seamless looping samples. This is a feature of the Sympakt that allows samples to be looped seamlessly, without any clicks or gaps. To support this, the UI should allow users to specify loop points for each sample, with crossfade options to ensure seamless looping. The metadata file should include the loop points and crossfade settings for each sample, so that they can be applied when the sample pack is loaded onto the Sympakt.
   * start and end loop points can be dragged in the waveform preview, with a visual representation of the loop points and crossfade area, with a maximum length of 5s.
   * Start and end loop points should automatically snap to zero crossings to minimize clicks when looping. 
   * the looped region can be dragged across the sample to allow for easy positioning of the loop points (while still auto snapping to zero crossings).
   * you can also drag the crossfade area to adjust the length of the crossfade, with a maximum length of the whole loop region. The crossfade should be applied using a linear volume fade in and fade out to ensure seamless looping.